  "original_title": "Dance of the Lions down under",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Dance of the Lions down under",
      "author": "Thilina Walpola",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Sri Lankans, in Australia \u2013 Melbourne, in particular \u2013 sure love to party, and that\u2019s exactly what they keep doing, on a regular basis.The Old Boys, from Trinity College, Kandy, made their presence felt at their big night, \u2018Dance of the Lions,\u2019 held at the Grand on Cathies Lane, in Melbourne.",
        "The event took place on July 16th, and there was plenty of action, from 7.00 pm to 1.00 am.",
        "According to Trevine Rodrigo, \u2018Dance of the Lions\u2019 showcased the lively spirit of the prestigious Kandy school, renowned for their proud reputation in academics and, more importantly, sports, where they have been much in the forefront during a rich history, among Sri Lankan educational institutions.",
        "Boxing, rugby, athletics and cricket has seen some outstanding sportsmen emerge from Trinity College. Says Trevine: \u201cThe Melbourne OBA added \u2018excellent organisation\u2019 to their CV with a memorable dinner dance which was complete, all round.",
        "\u201cThe Next Generation, a talented outfit, based in Melbourne, had the dance floor packed to capacity, and they were ably backed by DJ maestro Ash.",
        "\u201cAn excellent three-course meal, put on by the Grand, made it an immensely satisfying experience.\u201d",
        "Johann Jayasinha, Media SNNI/Australia, mentioned to us that \u2018Dance of the Lions\u2019 is the flagship event of the Trinity College Kandy Melbourne OBA, and is held biannually, adding that the proceeds of the dance will be donated to the T150 project of Trinity College, Kandy, who are celebrating, this year (2022) 150 years of Education, Learning and Character Building.",
        "Leave a Reply Cancel replyYour email address will not be published. Required fields are marked *Comment Name *",
        "Save my name, email, and website in this browser for the next time I comment."
      ],
